To make use of MySQL DB in Docker do the following steps (Windows OS instruction):
1. Make sure you have Docker installed. For Windows, Docker Desktop is
sufficient solution.
2. Open cmd or Powershell and navigate to docker-compose.yml file.
3. Run command: docker-compose up -d.
4. You can use database. If you do not do that, you will find an error during
starting the application from MySql connector.
5. If you want to stop the container type following command: docker-compose down